First time eating here it's been in the neighborhood for almost 9 years. My loss! Food was fresh and amazing. We each ordered an app.  I had the rock shrimp which was out of this world...light, crispy the aioli was perfect. 3 of us shared the chicken and beef  hibachi, the sauce... delicious. We each ordered the hibachi side noodles perfect with a hint of garlic. Now I need to go for lunch.

Ken ken ken. He is the best and you’ll see what I mean when you meet him. Never ordered something here that wasn't good. I come here often. They have great lunch specials with a lot to choose from. The ramen was great, the sashimi was great, sushi was great, habachi are all good especially thsteak. Aside from the food being great the presentation is great. They are happy to accommodate changes to the menu. Every now and then the chef will make something special for me to try. What stands out the most is their people. From the moment you walk in they greet you. They are knowledgeable about the menu and happy to make recommendations. Ken is so welcoming and always knows what to suggest for the adventurous foodie. This is a place I would recommend to anyone who visits NY or to my friends because I know they will be taken care of.

They also give a discount for students, if you still have a valid ID, and when I was in law school I got platters from them for student events.

The many times that I've been here they never disappoint. Salmon Hibachi and Chicken Hibachi are amongst my favorite dishes. The waitress is really friendly and the prices are amongst the most reasonable in the area.

Love boat for three. Freaky three-way number for a love boat, but I was left satisfied. The fish was fresh and the variety of fish really gave you a different taste and consistency with every bite. Some of the fish were cut into 4 pieces, so we had to do some diplomatic exchanges to who eats which fishs' last piece.  I'd trade a white tuna for a red snapper easy.  Damn, that sushi/sashimi boat was good. Highly recommended.  Although there wasn't anything special with the lighting or seating, I felt like it was the right theme for eating good sushi and getting out to the next adventure.  The waiter was attentive, but not annoying. He gave an excellent suggestion for the red snapper sashimi.  Enjoying this place and writing a great review was effortless.
amazing food, green tea fried icecream a must try

Maybe the best sushi place in the area, but sometime the products are not fresh or not ready. SO if you want to be safe, do not order Mango or Avocado. All the rest of the rolls are great, and the veg teriyaki is great as well. And their seaweed salad is something that shouldn't be ignored. Next time order it and you will thank me.
The delivery estimate they gave was 40 mins. It's been over 1 hour and 40 mins and I still have not yet received my order.

Great Sushi, maybe the best in Brooklyn. But, sometime their products aren't so fresh, especially when you order Avocado roll. Sometime it is amazing, and sometime i wonder how they let this thing out of their kitchen. I think that a place that respect itself should not allow non fresh products out. But still, i order from them at least once a week, since they are the best!

Very friendly staff, food is great for the price. One of my favorite spots to eat at. Every time I am around the area I eat here. Very clean atmosphere. Miso soup is like no other spot I ever tasted. Just about everything I tasted from here is good.

I've only eaten in once, and the experience was fine. The staff is very nice. Delivery is great. The food is solid, the delivery time is reasonable and reliable. No real complaints. There are nearby sushi places with more interesting speciality rolls, but for standard rolls, Mitoushi is a good choice.

Absolutely loved eating here. The wait staff is clearly experienced and respectful, the prices are the cheapest I've ever seen in Brooklyn, and the atmosphere is both soothing and refreshing. Stop what you're doing, pause the newest episode of Scandal, and enjoy a night at Mitoushi.
A neighborhood favorite of mine, order from here weekly.  Consistently good and some interesting rolls as well.  Delivery can be slow, but the atmosphere for eating in is pretty decent!

I stopped in to the restaurant one day for lunch. The sushi was good. I had the spicy tuna roll, california roll, and a shrimp roll. All were okay. The service was very good. The wait staff told me that customers could order sushi online and then have it delivered, if you live in the area. Good idea. Prices are reasonable. Not cheap but not too expensive.

A decent spot for sushi delivery. The spicy salmon roll was good, and the sashimi was good quality. The Lobster King roll (naruto) had way too much mayo on it and was pretty gross -- it literally fell apart. The spicy salmon salad was tasty.
Very good food and decent prices.
